tax_brackets.notes: NEEDS RESEARCH. The 1935 tax system was complex and multi-tiered. The top rate was 4 shillings and 6 pence in the pound (22.5%). There were additional surcharges and levies not yet modelled.

ietc.notes: NEEDS RESEARCH. The structure of low-income tax relief in 1935 is unknown.

wff.notes: NEEDS RESEARCH. WFF did not exist. The rules for historical family assistance programs are unknown.

ppl.notes: NEEDS RESEARCH. Paid Parental Leave scheme of 1935 is unknown.

child_support.notes: NEEDS RESEARCH. Child support rules for 1935 is unknown.

acc_levy.notes: NEEDS RESEARCH. The ACC levy rate and income cap for 1935 are unknown.

social_security_levy.notes: An emergency unemployment fund tax of 3.33% was in place.
